12	O

BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
The	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
speech	O
recognition	O
.	O

Speech	O
recognition	O
systems	O
analyze	O
a	O
person	O
's	O
speech	O
to	O
determine	O
what	O
the	O
person	O
said	O
.	O
Typically	O
,	O
a	O
processor	O
divides	O
a	O
signal	O
that	O
represents	O
the	O
speech	O
into	O
a	O
series	O
of	O
digital	O
frames	O
that	O
each	O
represent	O
a	O
small	O
time	O
increment	O
of	O
the	O
speech	O
.	O
The	O
processor	O
then	O
compares	O
the	O
digital	O
frames	O
to	O
a	O
set	O
of	O
speech	O
models	O
.	O
Each	O
speech	O
model	O
may	O
represent	O
a	O
word	O
from	O
a	O
vocabulary	O
of	O
words	O
.	O
A	O
speech	O
model	O
also	O
may	O
represent	O
a	O
sound	O
,	O
or	O
phoneme	O
,	O
that	O
corresponds	O
to	O
a	O
portion	O
of	O
a	O
word	O
.	O
The	O
processor	O
determines	O
what	O
the	O
person	O
said	O
by	O
finding	O
the	O
speech	O
models	O
that	O
correspond	O
best	O
to	O
the	O
digital	O
frames	O
that	O
represent	O
the	O
person	O
's	O
speech	O
.	O
Speech	O
recognition	O
is	O
discussed	O
in	O
U.S.	O
Pat	O
.	O
No.	O
4	O
,	O
805	O
,	O
218	O
,	O
entitled	O
"	O
Method	O
for	O
Speech	O
Analysis	O
and	O
Speech	O
Recognition	O
"	O
,	O
which	O
is	O
incorporated	O
by	O
reference	O
.	O

Each	O
comparison	O
with	O
a	O
speech	O
model	O
requires	O
a	O
relatively	O
large	O
number	O
of	O
calculations	O
.	O
A	O
speech	O
recognition	O
system	O
may	O
include	O
tens	O
of	O
thousand	O
of	O
words	O
in	O
its	O
vocabulary	O
,	O
with	O
each	O
word	O
having	O
a	O
corresponding	O
speech	O
model	O
.	O
Accordingly	O
,	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
calculations	O
required	O
to	O
compare	O
a	O
sequence	O
of	O
digital	O
frames	O
against	O
models	O
of	O
every	O
word	O
in	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
would	O
be	O
extensive	O
.	O
For	O
this	O
reason	O
,	O
the	O
processor	O
uses	O
a	O
pre-filtering	O
procedure	O
,	O
also	O
known	O
as	O
a	O
rapid	O
match	O
procedure	O
,	O
to	O
select	O
a	O
subset	O
of	O
words	O
from	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
.	O
The	O
processor	O
then	O
compares	O
speech	O
models	O
corresponding	O
to	O
the	O
pre-filtered	O
words	O
to	O
the	O
digital	O
frames	O
representing	O
the	O
person	O
's	O
speech	O
to	O
determine	O
what	O
the	O
person	O
has	O
said	O
.	O
One	O
approach	O
to	O
pre-filtering	O
is	O
discussed	O
in	O
U.S.	O
Pat	O
.	O
No.	O
5	O
,	O
202	O
,	O
952	O
,	O
entitled	O
"	O
Large-Vocabulary	O
Continuous	O
Speech	O
Prefiltering	O
and	O
Processing	O
System	O
"	O
,	O
which	O
is	O
incorporated	O
by	O
reference	O
.	O

SUMMARY	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
In	O
general	O
,	O
the	O
invention	O
features	O
using	O
lexical	O
tree	O
pre-filtering	O
to	O
identify	O
sets	O
of	O
words	O
for	O
use	O
in	O
recognizing	O
speech	O
.	O
Initially	O
,	O
a	O
vocabulary	O
of	O
words	O
is	O
represented	O
using	O
a	O
lexical	O
tree	O
.	O
Thereafter	O
,	O
a	O
first	O
subset	O
of	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
that	O
may	O
correspond	O
to	O
speech	O
spoken	O
beginning	O
at	O
a	O
first	O
time	O
is	O
identified	O
by	O
propagating	O
information	O
about	O
the	O
speech	O
spoken	O
beginning	O
at	O
the	O
first	O
time	O
through	O
the	O
lexical	O
tree	O
.	O
The	O
propagation	O
may	O
include	O
performing	O
a	O
relatively	O
coarse	O
comparison	O
of	O
the	O
speech	O
with	O
words	O
in	O
the	O
lexical	O
tree	O
.	O
A	O
second	O
subset	O
of	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
that	O
may	O
correspond	O
to	O
speech	O
spoken	O
beginning	O
at	O
a	O
second	O
time	O
is	O
identified	O
in	O
the	O
same	O
manner	O
.	O
Words	O
included	O
in	O
the	O
speech	O
are	O
recognized	O
by	O
comparing	O
speech	O
spoken	O
beginning	O
at	O
the	O
first	O
time	O
with	O
words	O
from	O
the	O
first	O
subset	O
of	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
and	O
speech	O
spoken	O
beginning	O
at	O
the	O
second	O
time	O
with	O
words	O
from	O
the	O
second	O
subset	O
of	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
.	O
The	O
state	O
of	O
the	O
lexical	O
tree	O
is	O
not	O
reset	O
between	O
identifying	O
the	O
first	O
and	O
second	O
subsets	O
.	O
Speech	O
spoken	O
beginning	O
at	O
the	O
first	O
time	O
may	O
overlap	O
speech	O
spoken	O
beginning	O
at	O
the	O
second	O
time	O
.	O

Embodiments	O
of	O
the	O
invention	O
may	O
include	O
one	O
or	O
more	O
of	O
the	O
following	O
features	O
.	O
The	O
coarse	O
comparison	O
may	O
include	O
propagating	O
scores	O
through	O
the	O
lexical	O
tree	O
.	O
The	O
scores	O
may	O
be	O
maintained	O
as	O
negative	O
logarithmic	O
values	O
,	O
which	O
simplifies	O
processing	O
of	O
the	O
scores	O
.	O

A	O
starting	O
time	O
may	O
be	O
associated	O
with	O
each	O
score	O
and	O
moved	O
with	O
the	O
score	O
as	O
the	O
score	O
propagates	O
through	O
the	O
lexical	O
tree	O
.	O
A	O
word	O
may	O
be	O
produced	O
by	O
the	O
coarse	O
comparison	O
when	O
a	O
score	O
corresponding	O
to	O
the	O
word	O
propagates	O
out	O
of	O
a	O
node	O
of	O
the	O
lexical	O
tree	O
corresponding	O
to	O
the	O
word	O
.	O
The	O
starting	O
time	O
propagates	O
out	O
with	O
the	O
score	O
and	O
corresponds	O
to	O
the	O
time	O
at	O
which	O
the	O
word	O
was	O
spoken	O
.	O

The	O
first	O
subset	O
of	O
the	O
vocabulary	O
may	O
be	O
a	O
first	O
list	O
of	O
words	O
,	O
and	O
words	O
produced	O
by	O
