DESCRIPTION	O
OF	O
THE	O
PREFERRED	O
EMBODIMENTS	O
Referring	O
to	O
FIG	O
.	O
1	O
,	O
a	O
speech	O
recognition	O
system	O
100	O
includes	O
an	O
input	O
device	O
such	O
as	O
a	O
microphone	O
105	O
.	O
When	O
a	O
person	O
speaks	O
into	O
the	O
microphone	O
105	O
,	O
the	O
microphone	O
produces	O
an	O
analog	O
electrical	O
signal	O
110	O
that	O
represents	O
the	O
person	O
's	O
speech	O
.	O
A	O
sound	O
card	O
115	O
is	O
connected	O
to	O
the	O
microphone	O
105	O
to	O
receive	O
the	O
analog	O
electrical	O
signal	O
110	O
.	O
The	O
sound	O
card	O
includes	O
an	O
analog-to-digital	O
(	O
A/D	O
)	O
converter	O
120	O
.	O
The	O
A/D	O
converter	O
120	O
periodically	O
samples	O
the	O
analog	O
electrical	O
signal	O
110	O
to	O
produce	O
a	O
digital	O
signal	O
125	O
.	O
For	O
example	O
,	O
the	O
A/D	O
converter	O
120	O
may	O
use	O
a	O
sampling	O
rate	O
of	O
about	O
11	O
kHz	O
so	O
that	O
the	O
