that	O
may	O
have	O
been	O
spoken	O
starting	O
at	O
a	O
start	O
time	O
265	O
.	O
The	O
pre-filter	O
procedure	O
255	O
responds	O
with	O
the	O
requested	O
list	O
260	O
.	O

The	O
speech	O
recognition	O
procedure	O
250	O
is	O
illustrated	O
in	O
FIG	O
.	O
3	O
.	O
The	O
processor	O
130	O
uses	O
the	O
procedure	O
250	O
to	O
produce	O
a	O
hypothesis	O
as	O
to	O
the	O
sequence	O
of	O
words	O
that	O
is	O
most	O
likely	O
to	O
have	O
been	O
spoken	O
in	O
a	O
time	O
period	O
that	O
begins	O
and	O
ends	O
with	O
silence	O
.	O
Initially	O
,	O
the	O
processor	O
retrieves	O
a	O
frame	O
of	O
digital	O
data	O
(	O
step	O
300	O
)	O
.	O
The	O
processor	O
then	O
determines	O
whether	O
the	O
frame	O
corresponds	O
to	O
silence	O
or	O
is	O
likely	O
to	O
correspond	O
to	O
silence	O
(	O
step	O
305	O
)	O
.	O
The	O
first	O
frame	O
always	O
corresponds	O
to	O
silence	O
.	O

If	O
a	O
word	O
needs	O
to	O
